	<h3><b>Cold</b></h3>

	The common cold, also known as an upper respiratory tract infection, is a viral infection that primarily affects the nose and throat.
	The symptoms of a common cold are Runny or stuffy nose, Sneezing, Sore throat, Cough, Mild headache, Fatigue or tiredness, Mild body aches, 
	Mild fever. Some common medicines for relief of cold are Cetirizine, Coldact, Chlorpheniramine, Diphenhydramine.
	<br />
