	<h3><b>Fever</b></h3>
	Fever is a common symptom that indicates the body's immune response to an infection, illness, or inflammation. 
	It is typically characterized by an elevated body temperature above the normal range of 36-37°C (97-98.6°F). 
	Symptoms of fever are Increased body temperature, Sweating or chills, Headache, Muscle aches, Fatigue or weakness, 
	Loss of appetite, Dehydration. Tablets for fever are Paracetamol, Dolo, Aspirin, Ibuprofen.
	<br />
	<a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/168266#diagnosis" target="_blank">Know more...</a>

</p>
